00:16:49,676 --> 00:16:51,720
He was cold and wet, so...

238
00:16:54,223 --> 00:16:57,476
Master, I'd like to take this moment
to say

239
00:16:57,559 --> 00:16:59,728
I was against this from the start.
It was all his fault.

240
00:16:59,812 --> 00:17:03,357
I tried to stop them.
Would they listen to me? No, no...

241
00:17:08,237 --> 00:17:10,406
Who are you?
What are you doing here?

242
00:17:10,489 --> 00:17:12,658
I... I... I was lost in the woods and...

243
00:17:12,741 --> 00:17:14,576
You are not welcome here!

244
00:17:14,660 --> 00:17:16,328
I... I'm... I'm sorry.

245
00:17:16,412 --> 00:17:19,331
- What are you staring at?
- Nothing.

246
00:17:19,415 --> 00:17:22,835
So, you've come to stare
at the Beast, have you?

247
00:17:22,918 --> 00:17:26,505
Please, I meant no harm!
I just needed a place to stay.

248
00:17:26,588 --> 00:17:31,343
- I'll give you a place to stay!
- No, no, please! No! No!

249
00:17:36,432 --> 00:17:40,727
Oh, boy. Belle's gonna get
the surprise of her life, huh, Gaston?

250
00:17:40,811 --> 00:17:43,063
Yep, this is her lucky day.

251
00:17:46,442 --> 00:17:49,862
I'd like to thank you all
for coming to my wedding.

252
00:17:49,945 --> 00:17:53,282
First, I better go in there
and propose to the girl.

253
00:17:55,701 --> 00:17:58,495
And you, LeFou, now,
when Belle and I come out that door...

254
00:17:58,579 --> 00:18:01,165
I know. I know. I strike up the band!

255
00:18:04,835 --> 00:18:06,795
- Not yet.
- Sorry.

256
00:18:19,141 --> 00:18:22,060
Gaston, what a pleasant surprise.

257
00:18:22,144 --> 00:18:25,439
Isn't it, though?
I'm just full of surprises.

258
00:18:25,522 --> 00:18:27,357
You know, Belle,
there's not a girl in town

259
00:18:27,441 --> 00:18:30,027
who wouldn't love to be in your shoes.

260
00:18:30,110 --> 00:18:31,778
This is the day...

261
00:18:34,823 --> 00:18:37,242
This is the day your dreams come true.

262
00:18:37,326 --> 00:18:40,078
What do you know
about my dreams, Gaston?

263
00:18:40,162 --> 00:18:42,915
Plenty! Here. Picture this.

264
00:18:43,916 --> 00:18:48,754
A rustic hunting lodge,
my latest kill roasting on the fire

265
00:18:48,837 --> 00:18:52,257
and my little wife massaging my feet

266
00:18:52,341 --> 00:18:54,718
while the little ones play on the floor
with the dogs.

267
00:18:54,801 --> 00:18:57,137
- We'll have six or seven.
- Dogs?

268
00:18:57,221 --> 00:18:58,764
No, Belle.

269
00:18:58,847 --> 00:19:01,600
- Strapping boys like me.
- Imagine that.

270
00:19:01,683 --> 00:19:03,018
Do you know who that little wife will be?

271
00:19:03,101 --> 00:19:05,062
- Let me think.
- You, Belle.

272
00:19:05,145 --> 00:19:08,982
Gaston, I'm... I'm speechless.

273
00:19:09,316 --> 00:19:11,443
I really don't know what to say.

274
00:19:11,527 --> 00:19:14,905
- Say you'll marry me.
- I'm very sorry, Gaston, but...

275
00:19:15,739 --> 00:19:18,700
But I just don't deserve you!

276
00:19:33,757 --> 00:19:35,384
So, how'd it go?

277
00:19:36,552 --> 00:19:39,429
I'll have Belle for my wife.

278
00:19:39,513 --> 00:19:42,307
Make no mistake about that.

279
00:19:43,976 --> 00:19:45,185
Touchy.

280
00:19:52,526 --> 00:19:53,902
Is he gone?

281
00:19:55,862 --> 00:19:58,991
Can you imagine?
He asked me to marry him.

282
00:19:59,074 --> 00:20:02,911
Me, the wife of that boorish, brainless...

283
00:20:03,412 --> 00:20:05,289
Madame Gaston

284
00:20:05,372 --> 00:20:07,207
<i>Can't you just see it?</i>

285
00:20:07,291 --> 00:20:09,251
Madame Gaston

286
00:20:09,334 --> 00:20:11,086
<i>His little Wife</i>

287
00:20:11,169 --> 00:20:14,673
<i>No, sir, not me, I guarantee it</i>

288
00:20:14,756 --> 00:20:19,261
<i>I want much more
than this provincial life</i>

289
00:20:28,270 --> 00:20:33,275
<i>I want adventure
in the great wide somewhere</i>

290
00:20:33,358 --> 00:20:37,154
<i>I want it more than I can tell</i>

291
00:20:38,113 --> 00:20:41,199
<i>And for once it might be grand</i>

292
00:20:41,283 --> 00:20:44,911
<i>To have someone understand</i>

293
00:20:45,662 --> 00:20:52,502
<i>I want so much more
than they've got planned</i>

294
00:20:54,296 --> 00:20:59,343
Philippe! What are you doing here?
Where's... Where's Papa?

295
00:20:59,426 --> 00:21:02,095
Where is he, Philippe?
What happened?

296
00:21:02,179 --> 00:21:05,307
We have to find him.
You have to take me to him.

297
00:21:18,987 --> 00:21:20,697
What is this place?

298
00:21:22,199 --> 00:21:24,201
Philippe, please, steady.

299
00:21:26,244 --> 00:21:27,454
Steady.

300
00:21:31,208 --> 00:21:32,334
Papa!

301
00:21:33,335 --> 00:21:35,671
Couldn't keep quiet, could we?

302
00:21:35,754 --> 00:21:38,215
Just had to invite him to stay,
didn't we?

303
00:21:38,298 --> 00:21:42,678
Serve him tea, sit in the master's chair.
Pet the pooch.

304
00:21:42,761 --> 00:21:44,429
I was trying to be hospitable.

305
00:21:45,847 --> 00:21:47,015
Hello?

306
00:21:47,724 --> 00:21:49,267
Is anyone here?

307
00:21:50,185 --> 00:21:51,353
Hello?

308
00:21:52,688 --> 00:21:55,607
Papa? Papa?

309
00:21:56,525 --> 00:21:58,026
Are you here?

310
00:21:58,652 --> 00:22:01,321
Mama, there's a girl in the castle.

311
00:22:01,405 --> 00:22:04,408
Now, Chip, I'll not have you
making up such wild stories.

312
00:22:04,491 --> 00:22:06,618
Really, Mama. I saw her.

313
00:22:06,702 --> 00:22:08,954
- Not another word. Into the tub.
- But... What?

314
00:22:09,037 --> 00:22:12,124
A girl. I saw a girl in the castle.

315
00:22:12,791 --> 00:22:14,376
See, I told you.

316
00:22:14,793 --> 00:22:18,922
Irresponsible, devil-may-care,
waxy-eared, slack-jawed...

317
00:22:19,005 --> 00:22:20,090
Papa?

318
00:22:21,717 --> 00:22:23,385
Did you see that?

319
00:22:25,262 --> 00:22:28,432
- It's a girl!
- I know it's a girl.

320
00:22:28,515 --> 00:22:31,685
Don't you see? She's the one.
The girl we have been waiting for.

321
00:22:31,768 --> 00:22:34,521
- She has come to break the spell.
- Wait a minute. Wait a minute.

322
00:22:38,400 --> 00:22:39,526
Papa?

323
00:22:41,153 --> 00:22:42,237
Papa?

324
00:22:44,906 --> 00:22:46,867
Hello? ls someone here?

325
00:22:47,659 --> 00:22:50,245
Wait! I'm looking for my father. I...

326
00:22:53,790 --> 00:22:56,543
That's funny.
I'm sure there was someone.

327
00:22:58,628 --> 00:23:00,172
Is anyone here?

328
00:23:00,756 --> 00:23:02,632
- Belle?
- Papa!

329
00:23:05,260 --> 00:23:06,678
How did you find me?

330
00:23:06,762 --> 00:23:09,598
Your hands are like ice.
We have to get you out of there.

331
00:23:09,681 --> 00:23:11,683
Belle, I want you to leave this place.

332
00:23:11,767 --> 00:23:12,851
Who's done this to you?

333
00:23:12,934 --> 00:23:15,437
No time to explain. You must go. Now!

334
00:23:15,520 --> 00:23:17,814
- I won't leave you.
- What are you doing here?

335
00:23:17,898 --> 00:23:19,107
Run, Belle!

336
00:23:19,191 --> 00:23:22,652
- Who's there? Who are you?
- The master of this castle.

337
00:23:23,779 --> 00:23:25,363
I've come for my father.

338
00:23:25,447 --> 00:23:27,699
Please let him out.
Can't you see he's sick?

339
00:23:27,783 --> 00:23:29,993
Then he shouldn't
have trespassed here!

340
00:23:30,076 --> 00:23:32,704
But he could die.
Please, I'll do anything.

341
00:23:32,788 --> 00:23:36,583
There's nothing you can do.
He's my prisoner.

342
00:23:36,666 --> 00:23:38,960
There must be some way I can...

343
00:23:39,878 --> 00:23:40,962
Wait!

344
00:23:46,218 --> 00:23:48,929
- Take me instead.
- You?

345
00:23:50,764 --> 00:23:53,767
You would take his place?

346
00:23:53,850 --> 00:23:56,061
Belle, no!
You don't know what you're doing!

347
00:23:56,144 --> 00:23:59,147
If I did, would you let him go?

348
00:23:59,231 --> 00:24:03,777
Yes. But you must promise
to stay here forever.

349
00:24:06,238 --> 00:24:07,989
Come into the light.

350
00:24:19,709 --> 00:24:22,587
No, Belle! I won't let you do this!

351
00:24:25,590 --> 00:24:27,676
- You have my word.
- Done.

352
00:24:31,888 --> 00:24:35,183
No, Belle, listen to me.
I'm old. I've lived my life.

353
00:24:35,267 --> 00:24:36,268
Wait.

354
00:24:36,351 --> 00:24:37,394
- Belle!
- Wait.

355
00:24:38,979 --> 00:24:41,690
No! Please spare my daughter. Please!

356
00:24:41,773 --> 00:24:45,110
She's no longer your concern.
Take him to the village.

357
00:24:45,193 --> 00:24:47,946
Let me out. Please let me out!

358
00:24:48,029 --> 00:24:52,200
Let me out! Please! Please!

359
00:24:58,039 --> 00:24:59,541
- Master?
- What?

360
00:25:00,208 --> 00:25:03,378
Since the girl is going to be with us
for quite some time,

361
00:25:03,461 --> 00:25:08,174
I was thinking that you might want
to offer her a more comfortable room.

362
00:25:10,135 --> 00:25:11,428
Then again, maybe not.

363
00:25:14,222 --> 00:25:16,474
You didn't even let me say goodbye.

364
00:25:16,558 --> 00:25:18,560
I'll never see him again.

365
00:25:19,102 --> 00:25:21,229
I didn't get to say goodbye.

366
00:25:22,564 --> 00:25:24,441
I'll show you to your room.

367
00:25:24,524 --> 00:25:27,068
My room? But I thought...

368
00:25:27,819 --> 00:25:29,487
You wanna...
You wanna stay in the tower?

369
00:25:29,571 --> 00:25:30,906
- No.
- Then follow me.

370
00:25:52,427 --> 00:25:54,262
Say something to her.

371
00:25:56,097 --> 00:25:59,184
I hope you like it here.

372
00:26:01,770 --> 00:26:02,896
The castle is your home now,

373
00:26:02,979 --> 00:26:05,941
so you can go anywhere you like,
except the west wing.

374
00:26:06,024 --> 00:26:08,652
- What's in the west...
- It's forbidden!

375
00:26:15,742 --> 00:26:19,120
Now, if you need anything,
my servants will attend you.

376
00:26:19,204 --> 00:26:21,414
Dinner. Invite her to dinner.

377
00:26:21,873 --> 00:26:25,627
You will join me for dinner.
That's not a request!

378
00:26:44,229 --> 00:26:46,106
Who does she think she is?

379
00:26:46,189 --> 00:26:48,358
That girl has tangled
with the wrong man.

380
00:26:48,441 --> 00:26:51,486
- No one says no to Gaston.
- Darn right.

381
00:26:51,569 --> 00:26:55,865
Dismissed. Rejected.
Publicly humiliated.

382
00:26:55,949 --> 00:26:57,909
Why, it's more than I can bear.

383
00:26:57,993 --> 00:27:01,413
- More beer?
- What for? Nothing helps.

384
00:27:01,496 --> 00:27:04,499
- I'm disgraced.
- Who, you? Never.

385
00:27:05,041 --> 00:27:08,753
Gaston, you've got
to pull yourself together.

386
00:27:09,170 --> 00:27:12,257
<i>Gosh, it disturbs me
to see you, Gaston</i>

387
00:27:12,340 --> 00:27:15,427
<i>Looking so down in the dumps</i>

388
00:27:15,510 --> 00:27:18,763
<i>Every guy here 'd
love to be you, Gaston</i>

389
00:27:18,847 --> 00:27:21,766
<i>Even when taking your lumps</i>

390
00:27:21,850 --> 00:27:24,894
<i>There's no man in town
as admired as you</i>

391
00:27:24,978 --> 00:27:28,481
<i>You're everyone's favorite guy</i>

392
00:27:28,565 --> 00:27:31,818
<i>Everyone's awed
and inspired by you</i>

393
00:27:31,901 --> 00:27:34,946
<i>And it's not very hard</i>

394
00:27:35,030 --> 00:27:38,867
<i>To see why</i>

395
00:27:40,618 --> 00:27:45,165
<i>No one's slick as Gaston</i>

396
00:27:45,248 --> 00:27:46,750
<i>No one's quick as Gaston</i>

397
00:27:46,833 --> 00:27:50,086
<i>No one's neck's
as incredibly thick as Gaston</i>

398
00:27:50,170 --> 00:27:53,798
<i>For there's no man in town
half as manly</i>

399
00:27:53,882 --> 00:27:56,593
<i>Perfect, a pure paragon</i>

400
00:27:56,676 --> 00:27:59,929
<i>You can ask any
Tom, Dick or Stanley</i>

401
00:28:00,013 --> 00:28:05,393
<i>And they'll tell you
whose team they prefer to be on</i>

402
00:28:05,477 --> 00:28:09,689
<i>No one's been like Gaston</i>

403
00:28:09,773 --> 00:28:11,357
<i>A kingpin like Gaston</i>

404
00:28:11,441 --> 00:28:14,652
<i>No one's got a swell cleft
in his chin like Gaston</i>

405
00:28:14,736 --> 00:28:18,573
<i>As a specimen, yes, I'm intimidating</i>

406
00:28:18,656 --> 00:28:21,618
<i>My, what a guy, that Gaston</i>

407
00:28:21,701 --> 00:28:24,996
<i>Give five hurrahs
Give 12 hip-hips</i>

408
00:28:25,080 --> 00:28:29,667
<i>Gaston is the best
and the rest is all drips</i>

409
00:28:30,418 --> 00:28:34,839
<i>No one fights like Gaston</i>

410
00:28:34,923 --> 00:28:36,508
<i>Douses lights like Gaston</i>

411
00:28:36,591 --> 00:28:39,844
<i>In a wrestling match
nobody bites like Gaston</i>

412
00:28:39,928 --> 00:28:43,223
<i>For there's no one
as burly and brawny</i>

413
00:28:43,306 --> 00:28:46,518
<i>As you see, I've got biceps to spare</i>

414
00:28:46,601 --> 00:28:50,313
<i>- Not a bit of him scraggly or scrawny
- That's right</i>

415
00:28:50,396 --> 00:28:53,358
<i>And every last inch of me's
covered with hair</i>

416
00:28:53,441 --> 00:28:56,569
<i>- No one hits like Gaston
- Matches wits like Gaston</i>

417
00:28:56,653 --> 00:29:00,031
<i>In a spitting match
nobody spits like Gaston</i>

418
00:29:00,115 --> 00:29:03,910
<i>I'm especially good at expectorating</i>

419
00:29:04,577 --> 00:29:07,038
<i>Ten points for Gaston</i>

420
00:29:07,122 --> 00:29:10,041
<i>When I was a lad
I ate four dozen eggs</i>

421
00:29:10,125 --> 00:29:13,628
<i>Every morning to help me get large</i>

422
00:29:13,711 --> 00:29:16,714
<i>And now that I'm grown
I eat five dozen eggs</i>

423
00:29:16,798 --> 00:29:22,804
<i>So I'm roughly the size of a barge</i>

424
00:29:22,887 --> 00:29:27,684
<i>No one shoots like Gaston</i>

425
00:29:27,767 --> 00:29:29,394
<i>Makes those beauts like Gaston</i>

426
00:29:29,477 --> 00:29:32,689
<i>Then goes tromping around
wearing boots like Gaston</i>

427
00:29:32,772 --> 00:29:36,734
<i>I use antlers in all of my decorating</i>

428
00:29:36,818 --> 00:29:39,237
<i>My, what a guy</i>

429
00:29:39,320 --> 00:29:45,285
<i>Gaston</i>

430
00:29:49,789 --> 00:29:52,208
- Help! Someone help me!
- Maurice?

431
00:29:52,292 --> 00:29:54,502
Please! Please, I need your help.

432
00:29:54,586 --> 00:29:57,255
He's got her...
He's got her locked in the dungeon.

433
00:29:57,338 --> 00:29:59,340
- Who?
- Belle. We must go.

434
00:29:59,424 --> 00:30:01,217
Not... Not a minute to lose.

435
00:30:01,301 --> 00:30:03,595
Whoa! Slow down, Maurice.

436
00:30:03,678 --> 00:30:06,472
- Who's got Belle locked in a dungeon?
- A beast!

437
00:30:06,556 --> 00:30:09,184
A horrible, monstrous beast!

438
00:30:14,814 --> 00:30:16,566
- Is it a big beast?
- Huge.

439
00:30:16,649 --> 00:30:19,569
- With a long, ugly snout?
- Hideously ugly.

440
00:30:19,652 --> 00:30:23,114
- And sharp, cruel fangs?
- Yes, yes! Will you help me?

441
00:30:23,198 --> 00:30:25,950
All right, old man. We'll help you out.

442
00:30:26,034 --> 00:30:29,787
You will?
Thank you, thank you, thank you.

443
00:30:32,040 --> 00:30:34,375
Crazy old Maurice.

444
00:30:34,459 --> 00:30:37,253
He's always good for a laugh.

445
00:30:38,546 --> 00:30:40,632
Crazy old Maurice?

446
00:30:42,091 --> 00:30:44,510
Crazy old Maurice.

447
00:30:45,887 --> 00:30:49,182
<i>LeFou, I'm afraid I've been thinking</i>

448
00:30:49,265 --> 00:30:50,850
<i>A dangerous pastime</i>

449
00:30:50,934 --> 00:30:52,101
<i>I know</i>

450
00:30:52,185 --> 00:30:55,480
<i>But that wacky old coot
is Belle's father</i>

451
00:30:55,563 --> 00:30:58,650
<i>And his sanity's only so-so</i>

452
00:30:58,733 --> 00:31:01,986
<i>Now, the wheels in my head
have been turning</i>

453
00:31:02,070 --> 00:31:05,198
<i>Since I looked at that loony old man</i>

454
00:31:05,281 --> 00:31:08,701
<i>See, I promised myself
I'd be married to Belle</i>

455
00:31:08,785 --> 00:31:13,331
<i>And right now, I'm evolving a plan</i>

456
00:31:13,414 --> 00:31:15,500
- If I...
- Yes?

457
00:31:15,583 --> 00:31:18,628
- Then we...
- No, would she?

458
00:31:18,711 --> 00:31:20,338
- Guess.
- Now I get it!

459
00:31:20,421 --> 00:31:22,674
- Let's go!
- Let's go!

460
00:31:22,757 --> 00:31:26,761
<i>No one plots like Gaston</i>

461
00:31:26,844 --> 00:31:28,471
<i>Takes cheap shots like Gaston</i>

462
00:31:28,554 --> 00:31:31,849
<i>Plans to persecute harmless crackpots
like Gaston</i>

463
00:31:31,933 --> 00:31:37,522
<i>So, his marriage
we soon will be celebrating</i>

464
00:31:37,605 --> 00:31:40,108
<i>My, what a guy</i>

465
00:31:40,191 --> 00:31:44,445
<i>Gaston</i>

466
00:31:47,615 --> 00:31:50,285
Will no one help me?

467
00:31:59,043 --> 00:32:01,254
- Who is it?
- Mrs. Potts, dear.

468
00:32:03,298 --> 00:32:05,258
I thought you might like a spot of tea.

469
00:32:05,341 --> 00:32:07,343
But you're... You're a...

470
00:32:09,137 --> 00:32:11,389
- Careful.
- This is impossible.

471
00:32:11,472 --> 00:32:14,058
I know it is, but here we are.

472
00:32:14,142 --> 00:32:16,978
I told you she was pretty, Mama,
didn't I?

473
00:32:17,061 --> 00:32:21,357
All right, Chip, now, that'll do.
Slowly now. Don't spill.

474
00:32:22,817 --> 00:32:24,235
Thank you.

475
00:32:24,319 --> 00:32:26,321
Wanna see me do a trick?

476
00:32:27,739 --> 00:32:30,742
- Chip!
- Sorry

477
00:32:30,825 --> 00:32:33,411
That was a very brave thing
you did, my dear.

478
00:32:33,494 --> 00:32:34,954
We all think so.

479
00:32:35,038 --> 00:32:38,583
But I've lost my father,
my dreams, everything.

480
00:32:38,666 --> 00:32:43,296
Cheer up, child.
It'll turn out all right in the end.

481
00:32:43,379 --> 00:32:44,964
You'll see.

482
00:32:45,048 --> 00:32:46,674
Listen to me jabbering on

483
00:32:46,758 --> 00:32:48,926
while there's a supper
to get on the table.

484
00:32:49,010 --> 00:32:50,762
Chip?

485
00:32:50,845 --> 00:32:52,180
Bye.

486
00:32:52,263 --> 00:32:55,433
Well, now,
what shall we dress you in for dinner?

487
00:32:55,516 --> 00:32:58,436
Let's see what I got in my drawers.

488
00:32:58,519 --> 00:33:00,229
How embarrassing!

489
00:33:02,774 --> 00:33:06,110
Here we are.
You'll look ravishing in this one.

490
00:33:06,194 --> 00:33:09,572
That's very kind of you,
but I'm not going to dinner.

491
00:33:10,239 --> 00:33:11,699
But you must.

492
00:33:14,869 --> 00:33:17,372
Dinner is served.

493
00:33:19,624 --> 00:33:21,501
What's taking so long?

494
00:33:21,584 --> 00:33:23,336
I told her to come down.

495
00:33:23,419 --> 00:33:26,923
- Why isn't she here yet?
- Try to be patient, sir.

496
00:33:27,006 --> 00:33:30,301
The girl has lost her father
and her freedom all in one day.

497
00:33:30,385 --> 00:33:31,886
Master, have you thought

498
00:33:31,969 --> 00:33:34,806
that perhaps this girl could be the one
to break the spell?

499
00:33:34,889 --> 00:33:37,642
Of course I have! I'm not a fool.

500
00:33:37,725 --> 00:33:40,478
Good! So, you fall in love with her,

501
00:33:40,561 --> 00:33:44,190
she falls in love with you, and poof!
The spell is broken.

502
00:33:44,273 --> 00:33:46,484
We'll be human again by midnight.

503
00:33:46,567 --> 00:33:49,070
It's not that easy, Lumiere.
These things take time.

504
00:33:49,153 --> 00:33:51,823
But the rose has already begun to wilt.

505
00:33:51,906 --> 00:33:53,741
It's no use.

506
00:33:53,825 --> 00:33:56,244
She's so beautiful and I'm...

507
00:33:56,327 --> 00:33:57,954
Well, look at me!

508
00:34:00,081 --> 00:34:03,042
You must help her to see past all that.

509
00:34:03,126 --> 00:34:04,877
I don't know how.

510
00:34:04,961 --> 00:34:07,505
Well, you can start
by making yourself more presentable.

511
00:34:07,588 --> 00:34:09,966
Straighten up.
Try to act like a gentleman.

512
00:34:10,049 --> 00:34:13,970
Yes. When she comes in,
give her a dashing, debonair smile.

513
00:34:14,053 --> 00:34:16,347
Come, come, show me the smile.

514
00:34:16,431 --> 00:34:20,393
- But don't frighten the poor girl.
- Impress her with your rapier wit.

515
00:34:20,476 --> 00:34:21,644
But be gentle.

516
00:34:21,727 --> 00:34:24,021
- Shower her with compliments.
- But be sincere.

517
00:34:24,105 --> 00:34:25,523
And above all,

518
00:34:25,606 --> 00:34:28,609
-you must control your temper!
- You must control your temper!

519
00:34:28,693 --> 00:34:30,111
Here she is!

520
00:34:32,155 --> 00:34:33,614
Good evening.

521
00:34:34,574 --> 00:34:37,410
- Well, where is she?
- Who?

522
00:34:38,828 --> 00:34:41,205
The girl, yes. The girl.

523
00:34:41,289 --> 00:34:45,168
Well, actually, she's in the process of...

524
00:34:45,251 --> 00:34:49,672
Circumstances being what they are...
She's not coming.

525
00:34:50,798 --> 00:34:51,883
What?

526
00:34:52,508 --> 00:34:55,052
Oh, dear. Your Grace! Your Eminence!

527
00:34:55,803 --> 00:34:57,513
Let's not be hasty!

528
00:35:00,516 --> 00:35:02,226
I thought I told you
to come down to dinner!

529
00:35:02,310 --> 00:35:03,853
I'm not hungry.

530
00:35:04,395 --> 00:35:07,690
You'll come out or I'll... I'll...
I'll break down the door!

531
00:35:07,773 --> 00:35:09,609
Master, I could be wrong,

532
00:35:09,692 --> 00:35:14,238
but that may not be the best way
to win the girl's affections.

533
00:35:14,322 --> 00:35:17,700
Please attempt to be a gentleman.

534
00:35:17,783 --> 00:35:20,495
But she is being so difficult.

535
00:35:20,578 --> 00:35:22,955
Gently, gently.

536
00:35:24,999 --> 00:35:27,418
- Will you come down to dinner?
- No!

537
00:35:28,669 --> 00:35:31,005
Suave, genteel.

538
00:35:31,088 --> 00:35:34,050
It would give me great pleasure

539
00:35:34,967 --> 00:35:36,928
if you would join me for dinner.

540
00:35:37,011 --> 00:35:38,721
And we say "please."

541
00:35:39,096 --> 00:35:40,598
- Please.
- No, thank you.

542
00:35:40,681 --> 00:35:42,892
- You can't stay in there forever!
- Yes, I can.

543
00:35:42,975 --> 00:35:47,480
Fine! Then go ahead and starve!

544
00:35:47,563 --> 00:35:52,193
If she doesn't eat with me,
then she doesn't eat at all!

545
00:35:55,655 --> 00:35:58,658
Oh, dear.
That didn't go very well at all, did it?

546
00:35:58,741 --> 00:36:01,619
Lumiere, stand watch at the door

547
00:36:01,702 --> 00:36:04,956
and inform me at once
if there is the slightest change.

548
00:36:05,039 --> 00:36:07,542
<i>You can count on me, mon capitaine.</i>

549
00:36:07,625 --> 00:36:11,837
Well, we might as well go downstairs
and start cleaning up.

550
00:36:13,256 --> 00:36:15,508
I ask nicely, but she refuses.

551
00:36:16,217 --> 00:36:18,594
What does she want me to do, beg?

552
00:36:19,845 --> 00:36:21,472
Show me the girl.

553
00:36:23,558 --> 00:36:27,270
<i>But the master's really not so bad,
once you get to know him.</i>

554
00:36:27,353 --> 00:36:29,355
<i>Why don't you give him a chance?</i>

555
00:36:29,438 --> 00:36:31,232
<i>I don't want to get to know him.</i>

556
00:36:31,315 --> 00:36:34,235
<i>I don't want to have anything
to do with him.</i>

557
00:36:36,070 --> 00:36:37,989
I'm just fooling myself.

558
00:36:38,072 --> 00:36:40,950
She'll never see me as anything

559
00:36:41,033 --> 00:36:42,535
but a monster.

560
00:36:47,790 --> 00:36:49,292
It's hopeless.

561
00:37:07,184 --> 00:37:09,020
- Oh, no.
- Oh, yes.

562
00:37:09,103 --> 00:37:11,772
- Oh, no.
- Oh, yes, yes, yes.

563
00:37:11,856 --> 00:37:14,317
I've been burned by you before.

564
00:37:17,445 --> 00:37:19,572
<i>Zut alors! She has emerged!</i>

565
00:37:24,160 --> 00:37:28,122
Come on, Chip. Into the cupboard
with your brothers and sisters.

566
00:37:29,248 --> 00:37:30,875
But I'm not sleepy.

567
00:37:30,958 --> 00:37:34,045
- Yes, you are.
- No, I'm not.

568
00:37:34,128 --> 00:37:37,673
I work and I slave all day long,
and for what?

569
00:37:37,757 --> 00:37:40,676
A culinary masterpiece gone to waste!

570
00:37:40,760 --> 00:37:43,763
Stop your grousing.
It's been a long night for all of us.

571
00:37:43,846 --> 00:37:47,016
Well, if you ask me,
she was just being stubborn.

572
00:37:47,099 --> 00:37:48,684
After all, he did say "please."

573
00:37:48,768 --> 00:37:51,520
But if the master doesn't learn
to control that temper,

574
00:37:51,604 --> 00:37:53,856
-he'll never break the...
- Splendid to see you

575
00:37:53,939 --> 00:37:55,566
<i>out and about, mademoiselle.</i>

576
00:37:55,650 --> 00:37:58,319
I am Cogsworth, head of the household.

577
00:38:00,738 --> 00:38:03,741
<i>- This is Lumiere.
- Enchanté, chérie.</i>

578
00:38:03,824 --> 00:38:07,036
If there's, stop that,
anything we, please,

579
00:38:07,119 --> 00:38:10,289
can do to make your stay
more comfortable...

580
00:38:10,373 --> 00:38:12,708
- I am a little hungry.
- You are?

581
00:38:12,792 --> 00:38:14,543
Hear that? She's hungry.

582
00:38:14,627 --> 00:38:17,713
Stoke the fire.
Break out the silver. Wake the china.

583
00:38:17,797 --> 00:38:20,424
Remember what the master said.

584
00:38:20,508 --> 00:38:23,552
Pish tosh. I'm not about
to let the poor child go hungry.

585
00:38:23,636 --> 00:38:26,555
All right, fine. Glass of water,
crust of bread and then...

586
00:38:26,639 --> 00:38:28,516
Cogsworth, I am surprised at you.

587
00:38:29,183 --> 00:38:31,936
She's not a prisoner. She's our guest.

588
00:38:32,019 --> 00:38:35,606
We must make her feel welcome here.
Right this way, mademoiselle.

589
00:38:35,690 --> 00:38:37,525
Well, keep it down.

590
00:38:37,608 --> 00:38:40,027
If the master finds out about this,
it will be our necks.

591
00:38:40,111 --> 00:38:41,946
Of course, of course.

592
00:38:42,029 --> 00:38:45,032
But what is dinner
without a little music?

593
00:38:45,700 --> 00:38:46,867
Music?

594
00:38:50,830 --> 00:38:54,291
It is with deepest pride
and greatest pleasure

595
00:38:54,375 --> 00:38:56,210
that we welcome you tonight.

596
00:38:56,293 --> 00:38:58,921
And now, we invite you to relax.

597
00:38:59,004 --> 00:39:03,843
Let us pull up a chair,
as the dining room proudly presents

598
00:39:03,926 --> 00:39:05,344
your dinner.

599
00:39:06,762 --> 00:39:11,642
<i>Be our guest, be our guest</i>

600
00:39:11,726 --> 00:39:13,936
<i>Put our service to the test</i>

601
00:39:14,019 --> 00:39:16,605
<i>Tie your napkin
'round your neck, chérie</i>

602
00:39:16,689 --> 00:39:18,607
<i>And we provide the rest</i>

603
00:39:18,691 --> 00:39:20,901
Soup du jour, hot hors d'oeuvres

604
00:39:20,985 --> 00:39:23,154
<i>Why, we only live to serve</i>

605
00:39:23,237 --> 00:39:25,489
<i>Try the gray stuff, it's delicious</i>

606
00:39:25,573 --> 00:39:27,825
<i>Don't believe me?
Ask the dishes</i>

607
00:39:27,908 --> 00:39:30,077
<i>They can sing, they can dance</i>

608
00:39:30,161 --> 00:39:32,580
<i>After all, miss, this is France</i>

609
00:39:32,663 --> 00:39:36,500
<i>And a dinner here
is never second best</i>

610
00:39:36,584 --> 00:39:39,044
<i>Go on, unfold your menu</i>

611
00:39:39,128 --> 00:39:42,256
<i>Take a glance
and then you'll be our guest</i>

612
00:39:42,339 --> 00:39:45,509
<i>Oui, our guest
Be our guest</i>

613
00:39:45,593 --> 00:39:47,887
<i>Beef ragout, cheese souffle</i>

614
00:39:47,970 --> 00:39:50,014
<i>Pie and pudding, en flambé</i>

615
00:39:50,097 --> 00:39:51,932
<i>We'll prepare and serve with flair</i>

616
00:39:52,016 --> 00:39:54,185
<i>A culinary cabaret</i>

617
00:39:54,268 --> 00:39:56,520
<i>You're alone and you're scared</i>

618
00:39:56,604 --> 00:39:58,606
<i>But the banquet's all prepared</i>

619
00:39:58,689 --> 00:40:00,733
<i>No one's gloomy or complaining</i>

620
00:40:00,816 --> 00:40:02,943
<i>While the flatware's entertaining</i>

621
00:40:03,027 --> 00:40:04,945
<i>We tell jokes, I do tricks</i>

622
00:40:05,029 --> 00:40:07,198
<i>With my fellow candlesticks</i>

623
00:40:07,281 --> 00:40:09,033
<i>Und it's all in perfect taste</i>

624
00:40:09,116 --> 00:40:11,202
<i>That you can bet</i>

625
00:40:11,285 --> 00:40:13,370
<i>Come on and lift your glass</i>

626
00:40:13,454 --> 00:40:15,456
<i>You've won your own free pass</i>

627
00:40:15,539 --> 00:40:16,624
<i>To be our guest</i>

628
00:40:16,707 --> 00:40:20,002
<i>If you're stressed
it's fine dining we suggest</i>

629
00:40:20,085 --> 00:40:22,171
<i>Be our guest, be our guest</i>

630
00:40:22,254 --> 00:40:24,089
<i>Be our guest</i>

631
00:40:25,800 --> 00:40:28,052
<i>Life is so unnerving</i>

632
00:40:28,135 --> 00:40:30,596
<i>For a servant who's not serving</i>

633
00:40:30,679 --> 00:40:33,891
<i>He's not whole
without a soul to wait upon</i>

634
00:40:33,974 --> 00:40:35,518
Get off!

635
00:40:36,310 --> 00:40:37,603
<i>Those good old days</i>

636
00:40:37,686 --> 00:40:39,438
<i>When we were useful</i>

637
00:40:40,606 --> 00:40:44,318
<i>Suddenly, those good old days
are gone</i>

638
00:40:45,027 --> 00:40:47,238
<i>Ten years we've been rusting</i>

639
00:40:47,321 --> 00:40:49,907
<i>Needing so much more than dusting</i>

640
00:40:49,990 --> 00:40:51,367
<i>Needing exercise</i>

641
00:40:51,450 --> 00:40:54,662
<i>A chance to use our skills</i>

642
00:40:55,287 --> 00:40:59,750
<i>Most days
we just lay around the castle</i>

643
00:40:59,834 --> 00:41:01,460
<i>Flabby, fat and lazy</i>

644
00:41:01,544 --> 00:41:03,462
<i>You walked in and oops-a-daisy</i>

645
00:41:03,546 --> 00:41:05,381
<i>It's a guest, it's a guest</i>

646
00:41:05,464 --> 00:41:07,132
<i>Sakes alive, well, I'll be blessed</i>

647
00:41:07,216 --> 00:41:08,926
<i>Wine's been poured
and thank the Lord</i>

648
00:41:09,009 --> 00:41:10,970
<i>I've had the napkins freshly pressed</i>

649
00:41:11,053 --> 00:41:12,972
<i>With dessert, she'll want tea</i>

650
00:41:13,055 --> 00:41:14,974
<i>And, my dear, that's fine with me</i>

651
00:41:15,057 --> 00:41:16,809
<i>While the cups do their soft-shoeing</i>

652
00:41:16,892 --> 00:41:18,853
<i>I'll be bubbling, I'll be brewing</i>

653
00:41:18,936 --> 00:41:20,729
<i>I'll get warm, piping hot</i>

654
00:41:20,813 --> 00:41:22,731
<i>Heaven sakes, is that a spot?</i>

655
00:41:22,815 --> 00:41:26,110
<i>Clean it up
We want the company impressed</i>

656
00:41:26,193 --> 00:41:28,320
<i>We've got a lot to do</i>

657
00:41:28,404 --> 00:41:30,239
<i>Is it one lump or two?</i>

658
00:41:30,322 --> 00:41:31,532
<i>For you, our guest</i>

659
00:41:31,615 --> 00:41:33,409
<i>- She's our guest
- She's our guest</i>

660
00:41:33,492 --> 00:41:34,743
<i>Be our guest</i>

661
00:41:34,827 --> 00:41:36,495
<i>Be our guest, be our guest
Our command is your request</i>

662
00:41:36,579 --> 00:41:37,955
Let's go, people. Fun's over.
Over here. Line up.

663
00:41:38,038 --> 00:41:40,791
<i>It's 10 years
since we've had anybody here</i>

664
00:41:40,875 --> 00:41:41,959
<i>And we 're obsessed</i>

665
00:41:42,042 --> 00:41:43,836
<i>With your meal, with your ease</i>

666
00:41:43,919 --> 00:41:45,880
<i>Yes, indeed, we aim to please</i>

667
00:41:45,963 --> 00:41:48,465
<i>While the candlelight's still glowing</i>

668
00:41:48,549 --> 00:41:53,095
<i>Let us help you, we'll keep going</i>

669
00:41:53,178 --> 00:41:57,391
<i>Course by course</i>

670
00:41:57,474 --> 00:41:59,643
<i>One by one</i>

671
00:41:59,727 --> 00:42:02,396
<i>Till you shout, "Enough, I'm done!”</i>

672
00:42:02,479 --> 00:42:06,233
<i>Then we'll sing you off to sleep
as you digest</i>

673
00:42:06,317 --> 00:42:08,319
<i>Tonight, you'll prop your feet up</i>

674
00:42:08,402 --> 00:42:10,154
<i>But for now, let's eat up</i>

675
00:42:10,237 --> 00:42:15,075
<i>Be our guest</i>

676
00:42:15,159 --> 00:42:18,704
<i>Please be our</i>

677
00:42:18,787 --> 00:42:24,543
<i>Guest</i>

678
00:42:27,338 --> 00:42:30,674
- Bravo! That was wonderful.
- Thank you.

679
00:42:31,634 --> 00:42:36,096
Thank you, mademoiselle.
Good show, wasn't it? Everyone!

680
00:42:37,056 --> 00:42:41,518
My goodness, look at the time.
Now it's off to bed, off to bed.

681
00:42:41,602 --> 00:42:44,021
I couldn't possibly go to bed now.

682
00:42:44,104 --> 00:42:46,023
It's my first time in an enchanted castle.

683
00:42:46,106 --> 00:42:47,441
Enchanted!

684
00:42:48,359 --> 00:42:51,528
Who said anything
about the castle being enchanted?

685
00:42:51,612 --> 00:42:53,197
It was you, wasn't it?

686
00:42:53,280 --> 00:42:55,407
I figured it out for myself.

687
00:42:57,242 --> 00:42:59,620
I'd like to look around, if that's all right.

688
00:43:00,287 --> 00:43:02,831
- Would you like a tour?
- Wait a second. Wait a second.

689
00:43:02,915 --> 00:43:05,376
I'm not sure that's such a good idea.

690
00:43:05,459 --> 00:43:09,171
We can't let her go poking around
in certain places,

691
00:43:09,254 --> 00:43:10,714
if you know what I mean.

692
00:43:10,798 --> 00:43:12,216
Perhaps you'd like to take me.

693
00:43:12,299 --> 00:43:15,719
I'm sure you know everything there is
to know about the castle.

694
00:43:15,803 --> 00:43:18,681
Well. Actually, I...

695
00:43:18,764 --> 00:43:20,099
Yes, I do.

696
00:43:21,308 --> 00:43:24,853
As you can see,
the pseudo-facade was stripped away

697
00:43:24,937 --> 00:43:27,398
to reveal the minimalist Rococo design.

698
00:43:27,481 --> 00:43:30,192
Note the unusual
inverted vaulted ceilings.

699
00:43:30,275 --> 00:43:33,904
This is yet another example
of the late-neoclassic Baroque period.

700
00:43:33,988 --> 00:43:37,533
And, as I always say,
if it's not Baroque, don't fix it.

701
00:43:40,202 --> 00:43:41,620
Where was I?

702
00:43:42,538 --> 00:43:43,956
As you were!

703
00:43:44,790 --> 00:43:49,420
Now, then, if I may draw your attention
to the flying buttresses above the...

704
00:43:49,503 --> 00:43:50,504
<i>Mademoiselle?</i>

705
00:43:56,677 --> 00:43:59,054
- What's up there?
- Where? There? Nothing.

706
00:43:59,138 --> 00:44:01,223
Absolutely nothing of interest at all
in the west wing.

707
00:44:01,306 --> 00:44:03,308
Dusty, dull, very boring.

708
00:44:04,476 --> 00:44:06,770
So, that's the west wing!

709
00:44:06,854 --> 00:44:08,230
Nice going.

710
00:44:08,856 --> 00:44:11,442
I wonder what he's hiding up there.

711
00:44:11,525 --> 00:44:15,446
- Hiding? The master is hiding nothing.
- Then it wouldn't be forbidden.

712
00:44:15,529 --> 00:44:19,950
Perhaps mademoiselle would like
to see something else?

713
00:44:20,034 --> 00:44:22,619
We have exquisite tapestries
dating all the way back to...

714
00:44:22,703 --> 00:44:24,872
- Maybe later.
