01:04:04,133 --> 01:04:07,053
<i>Beauty and the Beast</i>

952
01:04:09,805 --> 01:04:12,600
<i>Ever just the same</i>

953
01:04:14,852 --> 01:04:18,564
<i>Ever a surprise</i>

954
01:04:19,982 --> 01:04:22,526
<i>Ever as before</i>

955
01:04:22,610 --> 01:04:24,820
<i>Ever just as sure</i>

956
01:04:24,904 --> 01:04:28,491
<i>As the sun will rise</i>

957
01:04:29,867 --> 01:04:32,912
<i>Tale as old as time</i>

958
01:04:34,914 --> 01:04:37,750
<i>Tune as old as song</i>

959
01:04:40,086 --> 01:04:42,546
<i>Bittersweet and strange</i>

960
01:04:42,630 --> 01:04:44,924
<i>Finding you can change</i>

961
01:04:45,007 --> 01:04:47,843
<i>Learning you were wrong</i>

962
01:04:50,012 --> 01:04:53,349
<i>Certain as the sun</i>

963
01:04:55,017 --> 01:04:57,603
<i>Rising in the east</i>

964
01:04:57,687 --> 01:05:00,106
<i>Tale as old as time</i>

965
01:05:00,189 --> 01:05:03,234
<i>Song as old as rhyme</i>

966
01:05:03,317 --> 01:05:05,987
<i>Beauty and the Beast</i>

967
01:05:09,365 --> 01:05:12,243
<i>Tale as old as time</i>

968
01:05:12,326 --> 01:05:16,622
<i>Song as old as rhyme</i>

969
01:05:16,706 --> 01:05:23,254
<i>Beauty and the Beast</i>

970
01:05:24,171 --> 01:05:28,092
Off to the cupboard with you now, Chip.
It's past your bedtime.

971
01:05:30,386 --> 01:05:32,013
Good night, love.

972
01:05:56,037 --> 01:05:57,204
Belle?

973
01:05:59,749 --> 01:06:02,501
Are you happy here with me?

974
01:06:03,085 --> 01:06:04,170
Yes.

975
01:06:09,091 --> 01:06:10,426
What is it?

976
01:06:11,927 --> 01:06:15,639
If only I could see my father again,
just for a moment.

977
01:06:15,723 --> 01:06:17,433
I miss him so much.

978
01:06:22,813 --> 01:06:24,356
There is a way.

979
01:06:27,526 --> 01:06:29,987
This mirror will show you anything.

980
01:06:30,071 --> 01:06:32,073
Anything you wish to see.

981
01:06:33,032 --> 01:06:35,451
I'd like to see my father, please.

982
01:06:42,917 --> 01:06:45,211
Papa. Oh, no.

983
01:06:46,045 --> 01:06:49,799
He's sick. He may be dying,
and he's all alone.

984
01:06:56,514 --> 01:06:59,225
Then you must go to him.

985
01:06:59,892 --> 01:07:01,310
What did you say?

986
01:07:01,393 --> 01:07:04,855
I release you.
You're no longer my prisoner.

987
01:07:04,939 --> 01:07:08,776
- You mean I'm free?
- Yes.

988
01:07:10,402 --> 01:07:14,406
Thank you.
Hold on, Papa. I'm on my way.

989
01:07:17,409 --> 01:07:19,120
Take it with you

990
01:07:19,203 --> 01:07:23,082
so you'll always have a way
to look back and remember me.

991
01:07:27,419 --> 01:07:30,589
Thank you for understanding
how much he needs me.

992
01:07:38,931 --> 01:07:43,727
Well, Your Highness, I must say
everything is going just swimmingly.

993
01:07:43,811 --> 01:07:46,689
I knew you had it in you.

994
01:07:46,772 --> 01:07:48,858
I let her go.

995
01:07:48,941 --> 01:07:50,943
Yes, yes...

996
01:07:51,819 --> 01:07:54,071
You what?

997
01:07:54,155 --> 01:07:57,199
- How could you do that?
- I had to.

998
01:07:57,283 --> 01:08:00,077
Yes, but... But why?

999
01:08:00,661 --> 01:08:03,330
Because I love her.

1000
01:08:03,956 --> 01:08:05,624
He did what?

1001
01:08:05,708 --> 01:08:09,879
- Yes, I'm afraid it's true.
- She's going away?

1002
01:08:09,962 --> 01:08:12,006
But he was so close.

1003
01:08:12,089 --> 01:08:16,552
After all this time,
he's finally learned to love.

1004
01:08:16,635 --> 01:08:19,180
That's it then.
That should break the spell.

1005
01:08:19,263 --> 01:08:23,142
But it's not enough.
She has to love him in return.

1006
01:08:24,059 --> 01:08:25,728
Now it's too late.

1007
01:08:35,237 --> 01:08:36,322
Papa?

1008
01:08:37,156 --> 01:08:38,282
Papa?

1009
01:08:52,671 --> 01:08:54,089
They're back.

1010
01:08:56,508 --> 01:08:57,718
Belle.

1011
01:08:59,220 --> 01:09:01,513
It's all right, Papa. I'm home.

1012
01:09:03,098 --> 01:09:05,684
I thought I'd never see you again.

1013
01:09:06,477 --> 01:09:09,146
- I missed you so much!
- But the Beast...

1014
01:09:09,230 --> 01:09:11,899
- Did you... How did you escape?
- I didn't escape, Papa.

1015
01:09:11,982 --> 01:09:15,277
- He... He let me go.
- That horrible beast?

1016
01:09:15,361 --> 01:09:19,782
But he's different now, Papa.
He's changed somehow.

1017
01:09:25,204 --> 01:09:28,374
- Hi I
- A stowaway.

1018
01:09:28,791 --> 01:09:31,335
Why, hello there, little fella.

1019
01:09:32,086 --> 01:09:34,046
Didn't think I'd see you again.

1020
01:09:34,129 --> 01:09:36,715
Belle, why'd you go away?

1021
01:09:36,799 --> 01:09:39,218
Don't you like us any more?

1022
01:09:39,301 --> 01:09:42,179
Chip, of course I do. It's just that

1023
01:09:45,641 --> 01:09:49,228
- May I help you?
- I've come to collect your father.

1024
01:09:49,311 --> 01:09:52,147
- My father?
- Don't worry, mademoiselle.

1025
01:09:52,231 --> 01:09:54,733
We'll take good care of him.

1026
01:09:55,484 --> 01:09:59,113
- My father's not crazy!
- He was raving like a lunatic!

1027
01:09:59,196 --> 01:10:02,408
- We all heard him, didn't we?
- Yes!

1028
01:10:03,158 --> 01:10:05,953
- No, I won't let you!
- Belle?

1029
01:10:06,036 --> 01:10:09,373
Maurice, tell us again, old man.

1030
01:10:09,456 --> 01:10:12,126
Just how big was the beast?

1031
01:10:12,876 --> 01:10:16,088
He was... I mean, he was...
He was enormous!

1032
01:10:16,171 --> 01:10:20,467
I'd... I'd say at least eight,
no, more like 10 feet!

1033
01:10:22,261 --> 01:10:25,097
Well, you don't get much crazier
than that.

1034
01:10:25,973 --> 01:10:27,850
It's true, I tell you.

1035
01:10:28,475 --> 01:10:31,353
- Get him out of here!
- Let go of me!

1036
01:10:31,437 --> 01:10:33,647
No! You can't do this!

1037
01:10:35,065 --> 01:10:38,277
Poor Belle.
It's a shame about your father.

1038
01:10:38,360 --> 01:10:40,904
You know he's not crazy, Gaston.

1039
01:10:40,988 --> 01:10:45,868
I might be able to clear up
this little misunderstanding if...

1040
01:10:45,951 --> 01:10:48,787
- If what?
- If you marry me.

1041
01:10:48,871 --> 01:10:51,123
- What?
- One little word, Belle.

1042
01:10:51,206 --> 01:10:53,125
- That's all it takes.
- Never!

1043
01:10:53,208 --> 01:10:54,543
Have it your way.

1044
01:10:54,626 --> 01:10:57,880
Belle? Let go of me!

1045
01:10:58,505 --> 01:11:01,300
My father's not crazy
and I can prove it.

1046
01:11:01,383 --> 01:11:03,052
Show me the Beast.

1047
01:11:07,931 --> 01:11:11,393
- Is it dangerous?
- No, no, he'd never hurt anyone.

1048
01:11:11,477 --> 01:11:15,522
Please, I know he looks vicious,
but he's really kind and gentle.

1049
01:11:16,482 --> 01:11:18,650
- He's my friend.
- If I didn't know better,

1050
01:11:18,734 --> 01:11:21,737
I'd think you had feelings
for this monster.

1051
01:11:21,820 --> 01:11:24,615
He's no monster, Gaston. You are!

1052
01:11:25,532 --> 01:11:28,118
She's as crazy as the old man.

1053
01:11:28,535 --> 01:11:30,829
The Beast will make off
with your children.

1054
01:11:30,913 --> 01:11:32,414
- He'll come after them in the night.
- No.

1055
01:11:32,498 --> 01:11:35,376
We're not safe till his head
is mounted on my wall!

1056
01:11:35,459 --> 01:11:37,419
I say we kill the Beast!

1057
01:11:38,337 --> 01:11:40,005
<i>We're not safe until he's dead</i>

1058
01:11:40,089 --> 01:11:41,799
<i>He'll come stalking us at night</i>

1059
01:11:41,882 --> 01:11:43,509
<i>Set to sacrifice our children</i>

1060
01:11:43,592 --> 01:11:45,344
<i>To his monstrous appetite</i>

1061
01:11:45,427 --> 01:11:47,096
<i>He'll wreak havoc on our village</i>

1062
01:11:47,179 --> 01:11:49,014
<i>If we let him wander free</i>

1063
01:11:49,098 --> 01:11:52,768
<i>So, it's time to take some action, boys</i>

1064
01:11:52,851 --> 01:11:59,108
<i>It's time to follow me</i>

1065
01:11:59,566 --> 01:12:02,653
<i>Through the mist, through the woods
through the darkness and the shadows</i>

1066
01:12:02,736 --> 01:12:05,864
<i>It's a nightmare
but it's one exciting ride</i>

1067
01:12:05,948 --> 01:12:09,159
<i>Say a prayer, then we're there
at the drawbridge of a castle</i>

1068
01:12:09,243 --> 01:12:12,371
<i>And there's something
truly terrible inside</i>

1069
01:12:12,454 --> 01:12:15,624
<i>It's a beast
He's got fangs, razor-sharp ones</i>

1070
01:12:15,707 --> 01:12:19,002
<i>Massive paws, killer claws
for the feast</i>

1071
01:12:19,086 --> 01:12:20,671
<i>Hear him roar, see him foam</i>

1072
01:12:20,754 --> 01:12:22,297
<i>But we're not coming home</i>

1073
01:12:22,381 --> 01:12:26,552
<i>Till he's dead, good and dead
Kill the Beast!</i>

1074
01:12:26,635 --> 01:12:28,053
No, I won't let you do this.

1075
01:12:28,137 --> 01:12:31,974
If you're not with us, you're against us.
Bring the old man!

1076
01:12:32,057 --> 01:12:33,725
Get your hands off me!

1077
01:12:33,809 --> 01:12:36,353
We can't have them running off
to warn the creature.

1078
01:12:36,437 --> 01:12:39,940
- Let us out!
- We'll rid the village of this beast!

1079
01:12:40,023 --> 01:12:42,192
- Who's with me?
- I am!

1080
01:12:42,276 --> 01:12:43,569
- I am!
- I am!

1081
01:12:43,652 --> 01:12:45,112
<i>Light your torch, mount your horse</i>

1082
01:12:45,195 --> 01:12:46,947
<i>Screw your courage
to the sticking place</i>

1083
01:12:47,030 --> 01:12:49,908
<i>We're counting on Gaston
to lead the way</i>

1084
01:12:49,992 --> 01:12:53,078
<i>Through a mist, to a wood
where within a haunted castle</i>

1085
01:12:53,162 --> 01:12:56,373
<i>Something's lurking
that you don't see every day</i>

1086
01:12:56,457 --> 01:12:59,668
<i>It's a beast
One as tall as a mountain</i>

1087
01:12:59,751 --> 01:13:02,921
<i>We won't rest
till he's good and deceased</i>

1088
01:13:03,005 --> 01:13:04,590
<i>Sally forth, tally-ho</i>

1089
01:13:04,673 --> 01:13:06,258
<i>Grab your sword and your bow</i>

1090
01:13:06,341 --> 01:13:07,885
<i>Praise the Lord and here we go</i>

1091
01:13:08,010 --> 01:13:11,513
We'll lay siege to the castle
and bring back his head!

1092
01:13:12,306 --> 01:13:15,476
I have to warn the Beast.
This is all my fault.

1093
01:13:15,559 --> 01:13:20,105
- Papa, what are we going to do?
- Now, now. We'll think of something.

1094
01:13:27,905 --> 01:13:30,115
<i>We don't like
what we don't understand</i>

1095
01:13:30,199 --> 01:13:31,241
<i>In fact, it scares us</i>

1096
01:13:31,325 --> 01:13:34,453
<i>And this monster
is mysterious at least</i>

1097
01:13:34,536 --> 01:13:36,246
<i>Bring your guns, bring your knives</i>

1098
01:13:36,330 --> 01:13:37,623
<i>Save your children and your wives</i>

1099
01:13:37,706 --> 01:13:40,959
<i>We'll save our village and our lives</i>

1100
01:13:41,043 --> 01:13:42,127
<i>We'll kill the Beast</i>

1101
01:13:43,045 --> 01:13:46,298
I knew it. I knew it was foolish
to get our hopes up.

1102
01:13:46,381 --> 01:13:50,010
Maybe it would have been better
if she'd never come at all.

1103
01:13:50,093 --> 01:13:52,471
- Could it be...
- Is it she?

1104
01:13:52,554 --> 01:13:54,848
<i>Sacrebleu! Invaders!</i>

1105
01:13:54,932 --> 01:13:57,142
- Encroachers.
- And they have the mirror.

1106
01:13:57,226 --> 01:13:58,268
Warn the master.

1107
01:13:58,352 --> 01:14:00,437
If it's a fight they want,
we'll be ready for them.

1108
01:14:00,521 --> 01:14:02,356
Who's with me?

1109
01:14:02,439 --> 01:14:04,441
Take whatever booty you can find.

1110
01:14:04,525 --> 01:14:07,152
But remember, the Beast is mine!

1111
01:14:07,236 --> 01:14:09,154
<i>Hearts ablaze, banners high</i>

1112
01:14:09,238 --> 01:14:10,739
<i>We go marching into battle</i>

1113
01:14:10,822 --> 01:14:13,742
<i>Unafraid, although the danger
just increased</i>

1114
01:14:14,076 --> 01:14:15,577
<i>Raise the flag, sing the song</i>

1115
01:14:15,661 --> 01:14:17,037
<i>Here we come, we're 50 strong</i>

1116
01:14:17,120 --> 01:14:20,290
<i>And 50 Frenchmen can't be wrong</i>

1117
01:14:20,374 --> 01:14:22,125
<i>Let's kill the Beast</i>

1118
01:14:22,918 --> 01:14:25,504
- Pardon me, Master.
- Leave me in peace.

1119
01:14:25,587 --> 01:14:28,006
But, sir, the castle is under attack.

1120
01:14:28,590 --> 01:14:31,176
<i>Kill the Beast! Kill the Beast!</i>

1121
01:14:31,677 --> 01:14:36,014
- This isn't working.
- Lumiere, we must do something!

1122
01:14:36,098 --> 01:14:37,641
Wait! I know!

1123
01:14:38,475 --> 01:14:41,144
<i>Kill the Beast! Kill the Beast!</i>

1124
01:14:42,229 --> 01:14:44,314
What shall we do, Master?

1125
01:14:44,398 --> 01:14:46,525
It doesn't matter now.

1126
01:14:46,608 --> 01:14:48,026
Just let them come.

1127
01:14:48,110 --> 01:14:51,321
<i>Kill the Beast! Kill the Beast!</i>

1128
01:14:51,405 --> 01:14:53,198
<i>Kill the Beast!</i>

1129
01:15:05,627 --> 01:15:06,670
Now!

1130
01:15:27,608 --> 01:15:28,650
Yes!

1131
01:15:32,487 --> 01:15:34,156
Here we go!

1132
01:15:37,659 --> 01:15:39,161
What the devil?

1133
01:15:40,162 --> 01:15:41,747
Belle, look out!

1134
01:15:47,961 --> 01:15:50,172
You guys gotta try this thing.

1135
01:15:55,302 --> 01:15:57,721
Up here, you scurvy scum.

1136
01:15:58,388 --> 01:15:59,681
Now!

1137
01:17:09,292 --> 01:17:11,336
And stay out.

1138
01:17:41,950 --> 01:17:43,118
Get up.

1139
01:17:44,828 --> 01:17:46,037
Get up.

1140
01:17:46,621 --> 01:17:48,623
What's the matter, Beast?

1141
01:17:50,083 --> 01:17:52,961
Too kind and gentle to fight back?

1142
01:18:00,552 --> 01:18:01,595
No!

1143
01:18:04,765 --> 01:18:07,642
- Belle.
- No, Gaston, don't.

1144
01:18:13,648 --> 01:18:15,358
Let's go, Philippe.

1145
01:18:40,467 --> 01:18:42,344
Come on out and fight!

1146
01:18:44,596 --> 01:18:47,516
Were you in love with her, Beast?

1147
01:18:47,599 --> 01:18:50,101
Did you honestly think she'd want you

1148
01:18:50,185 --> 01:18:52,437
when she had someone like me?

1149
01:19:04,157 --> 01:19:08,286
It's over, Beast! Belle is mine!

1150
01:19:13,291 --> 01:19:16,795
Let me go. Let me go.
Please, don't hurt me.

1151
01:19:16,878 --> 01:19:18,964
I'll do anything. Anything!

1152
01:19:33,186 --> 01:19:34,396
Get out.

1153
01:19:35,981 --> 01:19:37,148
Beast!

1154
01:19:38,233 --> 01:19:39,401
Belle.

1155
01:19:48,410 --> 01:19:49,578
Belle?

1156
01:19:55,292 --> 01:19:56,793
You came back.

1157
01:20:36,124 --> 01:20:37,292
You...

1158
01:20:38,793 --> 01:20:40,378
You came back.

1159
01:20:40,462 --> 01:20:43,924
Of course I came back.
I couldn't let them...

1160
01:20:44,799 --> 01:20:46,593
This is all my fault.

1161
01:20:46,676 --> 01:20:48,470
If only I'd gotten here sooner.

1162
01:20:48,553 --> 01:20:53,183
Maybe it's better... It's better this way.

1163
01:20:53,266 --> 01:20:55,685
Don't talk like that.

1164
01:20:55,769 --> 01:20:58,063
You'll be all right.

1165
01:20:58,146 --> 01:21:01,983
We're together now.
Everything's going to be fine, you'll see.

1166
01:21:04,319 --> 01:21:07,447
At least I got to see you

1167
01:21:09,240 --> 01:21:10,742
one last time.

1168
01:21:21,836 --> 01:21:23,505
No. No.

1169
01:21:24,506 --> 01:21:28,510
Please. Please. Please don't leave me.

1170
01:21:32,514 --> 01:21:33,848
I love you.

1171
01:23:12,864 --> 01:23:15,241
Belle, it's me.

1172
01:23:31,216 --> 01:23:32,550
It is you.

1173
01:24:05,917 --> 01:24:07,168
Lumiere.

1174
01:24:08,044 --> 01:24:09,379
Cogsworth.

1175
01:24:10,880 --> 01:24:12,257
Mrs. Potts!

1176
01:24:13,633 --> 01:24:15,677
- Look at us.
- Mama. Mama.

1177
01:24:20,515 --> 01:24:24,018
- Oh, my goodness.
- It is a miracle.

1178
01:24:34,863 --> 01:24:36,114
<i>I 'amour.</i>

1179
01:24:40,368 --> 01:24:43,872
Well, Lumiere, old friend.
Shall we let bygones be bygones?

1180
01:24:43,955 --> 01:24:46,791
Of course, mon <i>ami.</i>
I told you she would break the spell.

1181
01:24:46,875 --> 01:24:51,462
I beg your pardon, old friend,
but I believe I told you.

1182
01:24:51,546 --> 01:24:53,339
No, you didn't. I told you.

1183
01:24:53,423 --> 01:24:55,216
You most certainly did not,

1184
01:24:55,300 --> 01:24:57,343
you pompous,
paraffin-headed pea-brain!

1185
01:24:57,427 --> 01:25:00,555
En garde, you overgrown pocket watch!

1186
01:25:00,638 --> 01:25:02,640
- Take that.
- Stop shoving.

1187
01:25:05,977 --> 01:25:09,230
Are they gonna live
happily ever after, Mama?

1188
01:25:09,314 --> 01:25:11,065
Of course, my dear.

1189
01:25:11,900 --> 01:25:13,234
Of course.

1190
01:25:14,068 --> 01:25:16,905
Do I still have to sleep in the cupboard?

1191
01:25:20,325 --> 01:25:24,037
<i>Certain as the sun</i>

